{"fsPath":"/home/khanh/src/0_github/leetcode/prep/vulcan/01_system_design/SYS-chat-messaging/impl/DESIGN_TECHNIQUES_AND_ARCHITECTURE.md","fileUuid":"8b6511ef-851a-40a4-83e0-85c110a11dc3","fileSizeBytes":10206,"numLines":393,"diffChanges":[{"originalStartLineNumberOneIndexed":1,"originalEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":1,"modifiedStartLineNumberOneIndexed":1,"modifiedEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":394,"addedLines":["# Design Techniques, Technologies, and Architecture","","This document explains all important design decisions in this project so that a reader can understand not just what the code does, but why it is built this way.","","Scope:","","- techniques and patterns (for example: outbox pattern, idempotency)","- technologies (for example: Redis Streams, PostgreSQL)","- architecture and data flow","- trade-offs and known limitations","- mapping from each concept to concrete source files","","---","","## 1) System goals and constraints","","This implementation targets a practical chat system baseline with:","","- `1-1 + group` chat","- realtime WebSocket communication","- reliability-oriented write path (transactional persistence first, asynchronous publish later)","- local single-node deployment with separate processes (`gateway`, `api`, `worker`, `postgres`, `redis`)","","Reference blueprint:","","- [`../implementation_blueprint.md`](../implementation_blueprint.md)","","---","","## 2) High-level architecture","","```mermaid","flowchart LR","    Client[ClientApp] --> Gateway[\"WS Gateway\"]","    Client --> Api[\"REST API\"]","    Gateway --> Core[\"Core Service\"]","    Api --> Core","    Core --> Postgres[(PostgreSQL)]","    Core --> Outbox[(outbox_events table)]","    Worker[\"Outbox Worker\"] --> Postgres","    Worker --> Streams[(Redis Streams)]","```","","Main processes:","","- `gateway`: handles WebSocket events.","- `api`: handles REST query/read endpoints.","- `worker`: publishes outbox events to Redis Streams.","- `migrate`: applies schema.","","Code:","","- [`cmd/gateway/main.go`](cmd/gateway/main.go)","- [`cmd/api/main.go`](cmd/api/main.go)","- [`cmd/worker/main.go`](cmd/worker/main.go)","- [`cmd/migrate/main.go`](cmd/migrate/main.go)","","---","","## 3) Technology choices and why","","## PostgreSQL","","Used for source-of-truth data:","","- conversations, members, messages, read state, receipts, outbox","","Why:","","- strong transactional guarantees","- simple relational modeling for chat entities","- robust indexing support for read paths","","Code:","","- [`internal/db/postgres.go`](internal/db/postgres.go)","- [`internal/db/schema.go`](internal/db/schema.go)","","## Redis Streams","","Used as asynchronous event transport after DB commit.","","Why:","","- simple event streaming model for local/small-medium setup","- consumer-friendly APIs (`XADD`, groups in later phases)","- lower ops overhead than Kafka for this stage","","Code:","","- Publisher side: [`internal/worker/outbox.go`](internal/worker/outbox.go)","","## WebSocket (gorilla/websocket)","","Used for bidirectional realtime messaging and ACK events.","","Why:","","- straightforward Go integration with `net/http`","- stable/mature ecosystem for quick implementation","","Code:","","- [`internal/transport/ws.go`](internal/transport/ws.go)","","---","","## 4) Core techniques and patterns","","## Technique A: Transactional Outbox Pattern","","Problem it solves:","","- Avoid losing publish events when business data is already committed.","","How it works here:","","1. In one DB transaction, business rows are written (`messages`, receipts, read state).","2. In the same transaction, an `outbox_events` row is inserted with `status='pending'`.","3. Background worker reads pending events and publishes to Redis Streams.","4. On success, worker marks row `published`.","","Code:","","- Outbox writes: [`internal/core/service.go`](internal/core/service.go) (`CreateMessage`, `RecordDeliveryAck`, `RecordReadAck`, `insertOutboxEventTx`)","- Outbox schema: [`internal/db/schema.go`](internal/db/schema.go)","- Outbox publisher: [`internal/worker/outbox.go`](internal/worker/outbox.go)","","Trade-off:","","- publish is asynchronous (slight delay)","- duplicate publish can happen if crash occurs between stream publish and DB status update","","## Technique B: Idempotency for submit and ACKs","","Problem it solves:","","- Client retry or network retry should not create duplicate business effects.","","How it works here:","","- Message submit idempotency: unique `(sender_id, client_message_id)`.","- Delivery/read receipts idempotency: unique `(message_id, user_id, device_id, receipt_type)`.","- Insert uses `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`; result interpreted as duplicate when `RowsAffected == 0`.","","Code:","","- Constraints: [`internal/db/schema.go`](internal/db/schema.go)","- Logic: [`internal/core/service.go`](internal/core/service.go)","","## Technique C: Per-conversation sequence ordering","","Problem it solves:","","- Message ordering must be deterministic within a conversation.","","How it works here:","","- Table `conversation_sequences` stores `last_seq` per conversation.","- On new message, transaction increments sequence and writes `messages.seq`.","","Code:","","- Schema: [`internal/db/schema.go`](internal/db/schema.go)","- Allocation logic: [`internal/core/service.go`](internal/core/service.go) (`CreateMessage`)","","## Technique D: Monotonic read pointer","","Problem it solves:","","- Out-of-order read ACKs should not move read state backwards.","","How it works here:","","- Read ACK resolves target message sequence.","- Current read pointer is loaded and compared.","- Update `members.last_read_message_id` only if target seq is greater.","","Code:","","- Logic: [`internal/core/service.go`](internal/core/service.go) (`RecordReadAck`, `shouldAdvanceReadPointer`)","- Test: [`internal/core/service_test.go`](internal/core/service_test.go)","","## Technique E: CQRS-lite split (write path vs async event path)","","Problem it solves:","","- Keep interactive request path fast and reliable while moving fanout/event propagation out of synchronous transaction path.","","How it works here:","","- Write path: `gateway/api -> core -> postgres (+outbox row)`.","- Async path: `worker -> redis streams`.","","Code:","","- Write path: [`internal/transport/ws.go`](internal/transport/ws.go), [`internal/transport/api.go`](internal/transport/api.go), [`internal/core/service.go`](internal/core/service.go)","- Async path: [`internal/worker/outbox.go`](internal/worker/outbox.go)","","---","","## 5) Event model in this project","","Current outbox `event_type` values used:","","- `message.created`","- `message.delivery_ack`","- `message.read_ack`","","Each outbox row contains:","","- aggregate info (`aggregate_type`, `aggregate_id`)","- event type","- payload json","- lifecycle fields (`status`, `retry_count`, `published_at`)","","Schema:","","- [`internal/db/schema.go`](internal/db/schema.go)","","---","","## 6) Realtime protocol model","","WebSocket inbound events implemented:","","- `send_message`","- `ack_delivery`","- `ack_read`","- `heartbeat`","","WebSocket responses implemented:","","- `server_ack`","- `delivery_ack_ok`","- `read_ack_ok`","- `heartbeat_ack`","- `error`","","Code:","","- [`internal/transport/ws.go`](internal/transport/ws.go)","- Example payloads: [`README.md`](README.md)","","---","","## 7) Data model walkthrough","","Main tables and responsibilities:","","- `messages`: immutable message facts + sequence.","- `members`: membership + `last_read_message_id`.","- `message_receipts`: per-user/per-device delivered/read receipts.","- `outbox_events`: reliable async publication queue in DB.","- `conversation_sequences`: ordering counter per conversation.","","Schema definition:","","- [`internal/db/schema.go`](internal/db/schema.go)","- SQL mirror: [`migrations/001_init.sql`](migrations/001_init.sql)","","---","","## 8) End-to-end flow examples","","## Send message","","```mermaid","sequenceDiagram","    participant Client","    participant Gateway","    participant Core","    participant Pg as PostgreSQL","    participant Worker","    participant Redis","","    Client->>Gateway: send_message","    Gateway->>Core: CreateMessage","    Core->>Pg: tx(insert messages + outbox_events)","    Core-->>Gateway: message + seq","    Gateway-->>Client: server_ack","    Worker->>Pg: select pending outbox","    Worker->>Redis: XADD stream","    Worker->>Pg: mark published","```","","## ACK pipeline (phase 3)","","```mermaid","sequenceDiagram","    participant Client","    participant Gateway","    participant Core","    participant Pg as PostgreSQL","","    Client->>Gateway: ack_delivery","    Gateway->>Core: RecordDeliveryAck","    Core->>Pg: insert receipt(delivered) idempotent","    Core->>Pg: insert outbox message.delivery_ack","    Gateway-->>Client: delivery_ack_ok","","    Client->>Gateway: ack_read","    Gateway->>Core: RecordReadAck","    Core->>Pg: validate target message seq","    Core->>Pg: advance read pointer if seq greater","    Core->>Pg: insert receipt(read) idempotent","    Core->>Pg: insert outbox message.read_ack","    Gateway-->>Client: read_ack_ok","```","","---","","## 9) Reliability characteristics and limitations","","What this design does well:","","- business state is persisted before async publish","- retries can continue from DB pending outbox rows","- idempotency reduces duplicate side effects","- read state monotonicity prevents regressions","","Known limitations (current stage):","","- outbox publisher can emit duplicates on crash windows (consumer must be idempotent)","- retry strategy is basic (`retry_count` only, no backoff/DLQ yet)","- worker currently polls pending rows (latency/load trade-off)","- full fanout consumer, presence map, and reconnect replay are Phase 4 scope","","Current outbox loop:","","- [`internal/worker/outbox.go`](internal/worker/outbox.go)","","---","","## 10) Alternatives considered (and trade-offs)","","## Redis Streams vs Kafka","","Redis Streams advantages here:","","- simpler setup for local/single-node development","- lower operational complexity","- adequate for current phase","","Kafka advantages:","","- stronger durability/replay model at large scale","- richer consumer-group ecosystem","- higher scalability ceiling","","Kafka trade-offs:","","- heavier operations and deployment complexity","- higher cost/overhead for this project stage","","Current choice rationale:","","- start with Redis Streams + outbox now, harden and benchmark first, then migrate only if evidence shows bottleneck or scale requirement.","","---","","## 11) Code reading guide for new contributors","","Recommended order:","","1. [`cmd/gateway/main.go`](cmd/gateway/main.go)","2. [`internal/transport/ws.go`](internal/transport/ws.go)","3. [`internal/core/service.go`](internal/core/service.go)","4. [`internal/worker/outbox.go`](internal/worker/outbox.go)","5. [`internal/db/schema.go`](internal/db/schema.go)","6. [`README.md`](README.md)","7. [`CODEBASE_BREAKDOWN.md`](CODEBASE_BREAKDOWN.md)","","This order follows request entry -> domain rules -> async publication -> storage model -> docs.","","---","","## 12) Operational entrypoints","","Main commands:","","- `make infra-up`","- `make migrate`","- `make run-worker`","- `make run-api`","- `make run-gateway`","- `make test`","- `make build`","","Source:","","- [`Makefile`](Makefile)",""],"tokenizedAddedLines":[1000000,1000001,1000002,1000001,1000003,1000001,1000004,1000005,1000006,1000007,1000008,1000001,1000009,1000001,1000010,1000001,1000011,1000001,1000012,1000013,1000014,1000015,1000001,1000016,1000001,1000017,1000001,1000009,1000001,1000018,1000001,1000019,1000020,1000021,1000022,1000023,1000024,1000025,1000026,1000027,1000028,1000029,1000001,1000030,1000001,1000031,1000032,1000033,1000034,1000001,1000035,1000001,1000036,1000037,1000038,1000039,1000001,1000009,1000001,1000040,1000001,1000041,1000001,1000042,1000001,1000043,1000001,1000044,1000001,1